# Remaining 16: 15x FS0039 — the FORCED-DEF NESTED-CHILD gap (probe: `type Default`/
# `type Const` exist NOWHERE; the canonical driver drives Anchored-rooted scopes only,
# while depth-2 children of pool parents have TRANSIENT/moored roots that the normal
# export-driven anchoring recursion would have materialized) — plus 1x FS0883.
# 2026-07-04 (3): FS0883 -> 0 (`+` joins the type-name boundary class: image/svg+xml -> ImageSvgXml).
# Remaining 15 = ONLY the forced-def nested-child family (trace in flight).
# 2026-07-04 (4): NESTED-CHILD ARM FIX (trace-agent-guided, one location:
# RenderScope.Anchored.fs canonical-home arm) — two defects unique to that arm: children
# anchored into a THROWAWAY dict while the registered scope kept an empty one, and the
# child anchor path dropped its LEAF (TypeStore VALUE carries it, as the export path and
# grandchild recursion already did). 15 -> 12; ProgressToken/Const materialized.
# Remaining 12 (Default/Tools/Resources/ReplyTo/Prompts) = the documented VARIANT: these
# children are referenced via ConcretePath refs which never TypeStore-register
# (Types/RenderScope.Prelude.fs:176-177), so the parent's store has nothing to drive —
# the child scopes exist Transient-rooted and undriven. Next fix: drive them from the
# child's own cached scope (or register concrete-ref children into the store).
# 2026-07-04 (5): 12 -> 10 via DEF/REF SYMMETRY ON INTERNED-SUBTREE CACHE-HITS
# (reRegisterStructuralLiterals, the render-seam companion of recordUnionMemberRefOwners):
# a cached molecule ref (union/generic-app/optional) embeds literal-child atoms but skipped
# the per-member descent that registers children into the CURRENT owner's TypeStore; the
# walk re-prerenders cached transient literals so every owner that embeds a child ref also
# holds its registration (ReplyTo/From class cleared). Also: anchor-time member re-walk on
# canonical homes, and the caller-dict filter dropped from the home arm's child recursion
# (a re-anchored home REPLACES its registered scope; a caller-gated recursion would leave
# the replacement's Anchors empty and drop already-emitted child defs).
# Remaining 10 (Default x2 / Continue/Inst/Path/Message/Input / Resources/Prompts/Tools):
# probed to the root — the children are THEMSELVES canonically-HOMED literals
# (shape=anchored, e.g. Resources=[uri,name,description]) whose defs emit at their own
# homes, while pool-home member refs re-root STALE RELATIVE atoms (minted by the child's
# per-owner first render) under the pool home at anchor time: `Home.Resources` ref vs
# `SharedLiterals.<StemHash>` def — a def/ref NAME disagreement at the REF layer, on
# structurally-identical literal twins with distinct rt identity. NB: TypeLiteral
# INTERNING was already tried and REVERTED (+36 e2e; same-shape literals under different
# owners ARE distinct types) — per that pinned negative result the fix belongs at the
# REF/path-anchoring layer: a re-rooted relative literal atom must be rewritten to the
# rt's actual def path (needs the atom->rt linkage, today's known missing link), or the
# molecule must re-render its literal atoms per anchoring site. Parked with breadcrumb.
# 2026-07-04 (6): RETRACTED EXPERIMENT, two pinned negative results (owner-caught via the
# Prototype metric moving; judged by GENERATION not error count). A workflow run (2
# investigators + 2 designers) overturned the twins framing: the Resources/Prompts/Tools
# referent is ONE interned INTERSECTION outside the shared-literal home system (homes gate
# on TypeLiteral), and the keying audit showed ALL ResolvedType dicts share payload-
# [<ReferenceEquality>] identity semantics (no comparer divergence anywhere). Generalizing
# reRegisterStructuralLiterals to kind-independent re-registration bought Zod 10->8 BUT
# over-materialized: TypeArguments descent + cross-owner first-write races planted
# wrong-home defs (`module Prototype` with `BotManagement`) and DUPLICATE members in
# downstream units that are gate-blind while Zod blocks — REVERTED. A second variant
# (re-rendering cache-hit refs from the stored path) regressed 8->12 via the force-loop's
# ONE shared bare-context store — REVERTED. Both pinned in prerender's cache-hit arm.
# Remaining-10 root, now precise: the multi-member shared-rt class — one rt referenced
# through several members (X["continue"]/X["inst"]/...; JSON-Schema const/default),
# per-site anchoring stamps each member leaf, the rt-keyed TypeStore holds ONE def.
# PREREQUISITES for the real fix: per-home store hygiene in emitCanonicalPreludeScopes
# (fresh store per forced home) + member-named PathContext on every registration channel;
# then def/ref coherence becomes decidable per home.
# 2026-07-04 (7): THIRD ref-side variant measured and REVERTED — the LEAF-GUARDED swap
# (only swap onto leaf-ful stored paths, the guard both prior failures implied) still
# regressed 10->11: stored paths can be MULTI-SEGMENT chains (`Default.Const` — the rt's
# first registration happened in a NESTED member context), so swapped refs print
# `Home.Default.Const` while child materialization emits a single-level `type Const` —
# a DEPTH mismatch between store grafting and def placement. Ref-side is now 3-for-3
# failed on this class. Def-side duplication (materialize the child under every stamping
# member leaf) was designed and rejected without running: it requires RECURSIVE grandchild
# duplication (same one-slot rt-keyed store, one level down).
# THE CLASS'S REAL FIXES, for the next design chunk (fresh context, isolation-test-first):
#  (A) INSIDE-OUT (preferred): resolve `X["k"]`-with-literal-index at the DECODER to the
#      SELECTED member type — each member then references a DISTINCT rt, per-member
#      stamping becomes correct-by-construction, and the class dissolves upstream
#      (also a fidelity WIN: real member types instead of proptypekey<X,K> renders).
#  (B) Around (ledgered degradation, forward-ref-scrub idiom): post-drive second round
#      degrading home-child path atoms without defs to obj + advisory ledger.
# 2026-07-04 (8): ZOD AT ZERO — THE UNIT COMPILES AND PRODUCES ITS ASSEMBLY (first L1
# unit-exit cell). Landed as option (B) from (7) plus the integration fixes the first
# real assembly attempt surfaced, each at its own layer:
#  - HOME-CHILD SCRUB (TypeRefRender.scrubUndefinedHomeChildren + post-drive second
#    round in emitCanonicalPreludeScopes): after the fixpoint drive the materialized
#    def-set is final; refs under a canonical home with no matching def degrade to obj,
#    LEDGERED per home (16 atoms / 8 homes, advisory-ledger.txt: home-child-scrub:*) —
#    the forward-ref-scrub idiom applied to the multi-member shared-rt class.
#  - SUPPORT LIBRARY made a PROJECT REFERENCE (was a source-link): the units pin
#    LangVersion 7.0 (shields the surface from newer-compiler tightenings — measured
#    46x FS0440 etc. under `latest`) while Xantham.Fable.Core needs F#9; its module
#    renamed Fable.Core.JsInterop.XanthamExtensions -> Xantham.FableCore.Extensions
#    (the piggybacked name is SHADOWED by Fable.Core.dll's module cross-assembly);
#    Fable.Core aligned at 5.0.0-beta.4 both sides (NU1605 downgrade made the support
#    types unloadable); its Directory.Build.props root-build exclusion REMOVED (its
#    "builds" were no-ops — the library had never actually compiled; it compiles clean).
#  - FUNCTION-PARAM PARENTHESIZATION (TypeRender.Render.fs parenIfFunction + the
#    anchored Function-molecule param arm): unparenthesized arrow chains in member
#    signatures read as CURRYING of the member itself (46x FS0440 with optional params,
#    6x FS0439 Invoke overload clashes).
#  - DUPLICATE-PROPERTY DEDUP (Member.partitionRender, ledgered
#    duplicate-property-drop): TS member merges land same-named properties with
#    different types in one interface; F# properties cannot overload (FS0438/FS3172).
#    First declaration wins, drops counted.
BL_FIDELITY_CLOUDEDGE_ZOD=0
