# 2026-07-04 (3): 86 -> 44. Two fixes, both tested (Tests/AnchoredRegistration.fs):
#  - ABBREVIATION-LEGALITY VERDICT (Render.aliasBodyVerdict, shared by the Transient AND
#    Concrete alias arms — the Concrete twin is where top-level aliases anchor): a body
#    atom carrying the alias's OWN path (the prerender cycle-break placeholder, e.g.
#    `type LoopbackForExport<'T> = option<U3<X,X,X>>`) or a declared typar absent from
#    the post-scrub body cannot be an abbreviation (FS0953/FS0035); such aliases emit as
#    EMPTY SAME-ARITY INTERFACES (refs stay legal everywhere — no ref-arity coordination,
#    sidestepping the pinned +196 trap). 118 aliases degraded, ledgered
#    cyclic-alias-body:*/phantom-typar-alias:*. FS0035 22->0, FS0953 4->0, FS0033 70->32;
#    golden IMPROVED (callbacks 72->70, synth-home 1101->1084).
#  - CHILD-PRESERVING REPLACEMENT (Anchored.addOrReplace): the scrub-armed second export
#    pass re-renders against the prelude cache, and cache-hits under-register nested
#    children that only FRESH minting stores — replacement scopes silently LOST
#    materialized child defs (ServiceWorkerGlobalScope's nested globals vanished while
#    their refs survived the scrub, whose def-set had honestly recorded them). Replacing
#    a scope now UNIONS the previous registration's Anchors (new entries win conflicts).
# Remaining 44: FS0039 x52 (Get/Service/Invoke/GetEntrypoint nested-under-type residue +
# LoopbackForExport arity-0 refs to the degraded arity-1 interface), FS0033 x32 (Fable
# lib arities: AsyncIterable given 3, BigInt64Array given 1; workers streams self-arity),
# FS0001 x4, FS1212 x2, FS0701 x2.
# 2026-07-04 (4): 44 -> 8. Three fixes:
#  - FABLE ARITY TABLE (verified against the Fable.Core 5.0.0-beta.4 DLL): AsyncIterable
#    joins singleParamIterators (3-param TS -> 1-param Fable); BigInt64Array joins
#    nonGenericTypedArrays (the old bare-name-invalid exclusion described the 4.x
#    surface); BigUint64Array stays excluded — 5.0.0-beta.4 has NO such type at all
